modules.description: Compares XML trees by identifying structural and content differences through node-by-node analysis. It processes parsed XML elements, attributes, and text nodes to generate detailed delta information. Used to track changes between versions of XML documents in configuration management or data synchronization workflows.

Creates DOM node trees from XML structures and applies patches to modify existing DOM nodes based on path and operation lists. Operates on XML trees, DOM nodes, and patch paths, using optional document and skip functions for customization. Used to dynamically update web page content by applying structured changes to the DOM.
